  "notes": "Oscan (5th c. BCE – 1st c. CE). Sabellic (Osco-Umbrian) language of Samnium, Campania, Lucania, Bruttium. ~400 inscriptions. Closest Italic relative of Latin. Substrate in Southern Italo-Romance: possible influence on Neapolitan and Sicilian vowel systems. Distinct from Latin in vowel diphthongisation patterns (Buck 1928, Rix 2002).",
